# Global HTML Standards (Voetberg Family Portal)

When creating or editing HTML pages in this repo, enforce the following. Full context: `context_7jK2n.md`.

## 1. Cache control (mandatory)

Every HTML page must include in `<head>` so mobile browsers drop cache and load fresh assets:

```html
<meta http-equiv="Cache-Control" content="no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate">
<meta http-equiv="Pragma" content="no-cache">
<meta http-equiv="Expires" content="0">
```

## 2. Search and bot protection (mandatory)

Every HTML page must include the **full bot block** in `<head>`. Do not use a shortened set (e.g. robots only). This keeps family content out of search results and AI training:

```html
<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow, noarchive, nosnippet, noimageindex">
<meta name="googlebot" content="noindex, nofollow">
<meta name="google-extended" content="noindex, nofollow">
<meta name="gptbot" content="noindex, nofollow">
<meta name="CCBot" content="noindex, nofollow">
```

## 3. Assets

- All images and video **must** reside under `/images/` (or the project’s asset directory). Do not place assets in repo root.
- Reference with paths relative to repo root (e.g. `images/don_moose_rider II.mp4`).

## 4. Back-button fix (dynamic pages)

For **dynamic** pages (Training, Orders, Pantry, Supplements) place before `</body>`:

```html
<script>
window.onpageshow = function(event) {
  if (event.persisted) { window.location.reload(); }
};
</script>
```

## 5. Video backgrounds

- Use `object-fit: cover` (or `contain` for portrait).
- Attributes: `muted` `loop` `playsinline`.
- Include a dark CSS overlay (e.g. `rgba(0,0,0,0.3)`–`0.7`) for text readability.

## 6. Footer “Last updated”

Where applicable, include a footer script that displays document last-modified (e.g. `lastUpdated` element + `document.lastModified`).
